text: Veronika Hrončeková (born 2 January 1990) is a Slovak female volleyball player. She is part of the Slovakia women's national volleyball team.She competed at the 2007 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2009 Women's European Volleyball Championship, 2019 Women's European Volleyball Championship. ==Clubs== * Zvolen (none–2004) * Slávia UK Bratislava (2004–2010) * VK Agel Prostejov (2010–2013) * Schweriner SC (2013–2016) * VfB 91 Suhl (2016–2017) * CSM Târgoviște (2017–2018) * Strabag VC FTVŠ UK Bratislava (2018–2019) * Hapoel Kfar Saba (2019–present) == References == == External links == * Profile on CEV Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak women's volleyball players Category:People from Zvolen
